Commentary: Vishwa starts with a fuller delivery on off. Masood starts his innings with a solid front foot defense. Hint of shape first up for Vishwa.
Goes outside off and makes it come back in. Masood shows awareness of his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Vishwa wants Shan to drive but Masood is happy to watch it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Masood defends it back to the bowler and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick it to the on side but closes the phase of the bat early and it goes back to the bowler off the leading edge.
Maiden to start with. Tidy start from Vishwa. The last ball is fuller around off, Shan strokes it towards point. The fielder there dives to his left and saves runs for his side.

A bit of noise there. Not sure whether it was of the ball clipping the pad or the bat hitting the pad. Kumara starts with a length ball down the leg side, Abid looks to flick but misses. Dickwella behind the stumps dives to his left but fails to take it cleanly. Wouldn't have mattered as the ball did not kiss the bat.
Another one down the leg side and once again Abid tries to flick but to no avail.
Right off the meat! Good length ball on off, Abid shows that he is a man in form as he defends it right of the middle of the blade towards cover.
Good length ball which comes in to the right-hander. It is around the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.

Pakistan get their scoreboard underway, albeit a leg bye. Slightly fuller and angling in. Abid looks to flick but misses. The ball goes to the leg side off the pads. There is a slight appeal but the umpire turns it down as it is doing too much and in the meantime they steal a leg bye.
Beauty to end with. Back of a length delivery around off, it looks to go with the angle but straightens after hitting the deck. Shan looks to defend but gets beaten.
Very good ball this. Very full, almost a yorker around off. Abid does really well to jam it out towards mid on.
Good length ball outside off, asking Abid to have a crack at it but he shoulders arms to it.
A Steven Smith-esque leave this. Fuller outside off, Abid leaves it alone in an unorthodox manner.

Down the leg side. Abid looks to flick but misses. Looks like they are intentionally bowling one or two down the leg side to Abid Ali so that he can kiss one of his flick which can go to the keeper. Not sure whether this is a right plan or not.
Better line and length this. On the good length area and outside off, Abid leaves it alone.
Even better line. On the off pole and full. Abid defends it really nicely off his front foot.

Stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Looked to be high and also pitching outside leg. It is on the pads, Shan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. The bowler goes up in appeal but the umpire is unmoved.

EDGED AND FOUR! First runs off the bat and it has come in a streaky way. First runs in Test cricket in Pakistan for Shan Masood. Beautiful ball this. Good length ball, on the channel of uncertainty. Shan looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes right in the gap between third slip and gully to the fence for a boundary. This will encourage Lahiru more than Shan.
Short ball outside off, Masood ducks away.
Length ball on off, Masood defends it towards point and shouts a loud no.
On the fourth stump line, SM shoulders arms to it.
Full on off, Masood defends it with a straight bat towards mid on.
Good length ball outside off, it goes away with the angle. Abid does not go chasing after it and lets it carry to the keeper.
Closer to the off pole but still outside so Shan leaves it alone.
Finally Vishwa delivers and bowls it on a length on off. Abid defends it towards point.
Good length ball on middle and off, Abid defends it to the right of the bowler.
FOUR! After a long time Abid Ali is off the mark. Good length ball outside off, Abid cuts it over point and gets off the mark with a boundary. Shot of a man in form.
Wild delivery way outside off. Abid leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Masood punches it towards point. The batsmen take a run.
Good length delivery on off, Ali defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Abid blocks it well.
Good length delivery on off, Abid defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Abid blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Abid keeps it out.

OUT! Bowled! Beauty of a delivery! WOW! That is every pace bowler's dream delivery. Too good for Shan Masood. Vishwa charges in and shows good seam position. The ball hits the surface and shapes away at the end. Masood looks to defend but gets squared up and the ball hits the top of off pole. Cracker of a delivery to begin the over and Shan's poor series continues. You can watch this delivery on loop and you will never get bored. Shan Masood will not want to watch it though.
The Pakistan Test skipper starts his innings with a calm leave to begin his innings.

OUT! Bowled! Another gem and what an over this is turning out to be. Right through the gate. Vishwa is bowling venom here. Good length ball on off, it comes in to the right-hander. Azhar Ali looks to defend but the ball goes right between the gate of bat and pads to dislodge the off stump. Azhar Ali's poor 2019 continues and the misery piles on him. A silver duck for the skipper. Wicket, dot, wicket. What an over this is turning out to be.
One bad ball. After two gems this can be let go. Down the leg side, Babar looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Another length ball outside off and Babar calmly shoulders arms to it. End of a terrific over from Vishwa. Double wicket maiden.
On a good length on off, Abid offers a solid defense on this one.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Abid does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Beautiful shot this. Good length ball around off, Abid gets on his back foot and punches it gorgeously through covers for a boundary. He is continuing from where he left off in Rawalpindi.
Good length delivery on middle, Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it back towards the bowler and Kumara picks the ball and hits the stumps at the striker's end in his followthrough. But Abid Ali was well in.
On a good length on off, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery down the leg side, Azam looks to flick but misses it. It goes towards the keeper safely.
FOUR! Babar is off the mark with a boundary. Poor ball this. On the pads, Azam just tickles it fine down the leg side and fetches himself a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Azam blocks it off the front foot.

Excitement from the keeper but not so much from Dickwella. Another one down the leg side, Azam looks to flick but there is two noises. Dickwella dives to his left and catches it. There is an appeal but the umpire turns it down. Replays later on show that the bat hit the pad and the ball kissed the pad.
On the stumps, Babar defends it with a dead bat.
Bowls it down the leg side, Babar looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Ali blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Length delivery on off, Ali slaps it through covers for a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
SIX! Poor ball this. Half tracker on off and middle. Abid will punish it even in his sleep and he pulls it over the mid-wicket fence for a the first biggie of the game.
On a length on middle, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
On a good length and outside off, Ali taps it to point.
FOUR! That is put away! Length delivery outside off, Abid punches it through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, Ali offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.

NOT OUT! Good use of the review. A full toss from Vishwa around leg. Babar looks to flick but misses and the ball hits him on the pads. The Sri Lankan players go up in a confident appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Babar does not even consult his partner and straightaway signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows spike as the ball goes past the bat. The on-field umpire will have to overturn his decision. The fans in here take a sigh of relief as their talisman survives.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Short delivery outside off, Ali cuts it hard through point for a boundary.

FOUR! Short, wide and punished. Poor start from Embuldeniya. He offers width outside off, Abid quickly gets on his back foot and cuts it through point once again for a boundary. He is super strong in that area and will punish you 9/10 times.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! Flighted delivery just outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it due to the spin on this one.
Floated delivery on off, Abid plays it to covers.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery outside off, Babar drives it towards mid off.
On a good length on off, Azam defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Nicely played. A little too full on off, Babar waits and then just squeezes it through the gap past gully for a boundary. This is the class of this man. Did not play this shot with power but with just timing and sense. Runs starting to flow here for Pakistan.
Bowls it down the leg side, Azam looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length and outside off, Azam shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Azam looks to drive but misses it.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid plays it to point.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery just outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Loopy delivery on off, Ali blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Azam blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, Babar leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Azam shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Azam drives it towards covers for a run.
Outside off, Abid offers no shot to this one.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Azam comes down the track and blocks it.
Floated delivery on off, Azam punches it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ali blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Abid sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Babar leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Azam keeps it out.
Again outside off, Babar offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Azam taps it towards point for a run.
On a length and outside off, Ali plays it to point.
Length delivery on middle, Abid flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings this for a man of Babar's caliber. Short outside off, Babar gets on his back foot and creams his punch through covers for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Babar brings up the 50-run stand up in style. Slightly overpitched on off. Babar does not need much to go wrong for him to make the bowler's punish. He creams it through covers and holds the pose for the camera.
Full delivery on middle, Azam flicks it to mid on.
Full again and outside off, Azam drives it to point.
On a good length on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Azam drives it towards mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ali defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ali sweeps it through square leg. The batsmen take a run.

Flighted delivery on middle, Ali flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Flighted delivery on middle, Ali looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Replays show that there was a clear inside edge on this one.
Full delivery on middle, Abid drives it towards mid on.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan don't just lose a big wicket but they also lose one of their reviews. This is a body blow for them. The budding stand has been cut short and this time Abid cannot convert his start. He survived an inswinging delivery early in this over but this time his luck has ran out. Very good ball this from Kumara. Fast and swinging in from around off. Abid looks to defend but misses and the ball hits him on the front pad. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Abid has a word with Babar, they discuss for a while and then in the dying seconds he signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first shows no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes up next and it shows all red as the ball was hitting the middle stump. Crucial wicket for the visitors, Abid was looking very good out in the middle and one would feel this wicket has come against the run of play.
Full on middle, Asad pushes it to mid on to start his innings.
Back of a length on off, Shafiq this time blocks it off his back foot.
On the pads, Asad flicks it to mid-wicket to get through the over. Successful over for Sri Lanka.
Flighted delivery on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Azam comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq drives it uppishly towards the bowler where it falls just short of Embuldeniya.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the back foot.

In the air but safe. Babar is lucky to survive this. Excellent short ball from Lahiru. It is pacy and well directed. On the body, Babar is late to get his bat up. He ends up playing a very awkward flick to the short one. He ends up chipping it to the vacant area at mid-wicket and gets a single. Very good from Lahiru to surprise BA.
Outside off, Shafiq shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Shafiq defends it to covers.
Length delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.
On a length and outside off, Azam punches it through covers. Embuldeniya tries to stop it but fumbles. The batsmen get three runs.
On a good length on middle, Shafiq blocks it well.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam defends it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Azam punches it through point for a run.

Loopy delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Asad blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it off the front foot. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Kumara starts with a good length ball outside off. Babar starts the session with calmness as he does not disturb this one.
Length delivery outside off, Azam shoulders arms to it.
A very low full toss on off, Babar pushes it to mid off. First ball he has hit in this session and it has come closer to the middle so solid start.
Full and swinging in on off. Azam pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Babar defends it with a straight bat.
Length delivery around off, Babar looks to play it on the off side but it goes straight off the inner half of the bat. Maiden to start the second session.
Floated delivery on off, Shafiq blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq punches it through point. The fielder chases it, slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Azam comes down the track and drives it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.

What a beautiful ball. That cut Asad Shafiq in half. Pacy and coming in from outside off. Asad looks to defend but the ball goes right between his bat and pad and over the stumps. Dickwella does really well diving to his left. It was going away from him.
On a good length on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.

Good length delivery on off, Shafiq looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Replays show that there was a clear inside edge on this one.
On a good length on middle, Shafiq keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.

Bowls a bouncer outside off, Azam lets it sail through to the keeper.
FOUR! First boundary of the session and what a crunching shot it is. Full outside off, Babar gets on his front foot and slams his drive through point for a boundary.

In the air and ... Babar survies! Typical fast bowler's response but a very well directed one as well. Back of a length ball around the body. The ball shoots up onto the batsman. Babar puts his bat to defend his face. The ball takes the top edge and lobs up in the air. The bowler tries his bets to the get there but it falls away from him in no man's land.
Full delivery on off, Azam drives it to mid off.
Bowls a bouncer, Azam ducks under it.
Bowls a bumper again, Azam watches it sail through to the keeper.
Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq punches it through point for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam plays it to point.

SIX! Don't bother looking that has gone over the ropes with ease. Excellent use of the feet from Asad. This is a pressure releasing shot from him. Floated on middle, Asad comes down the track, maintains his balance and smokes it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Floated delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Azam looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.

On a good length on middle, Azam defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Another smart shot from Babar. He is oozing confidence. Good length ball outside off, Babar waits and then cuts it through point for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Azam flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs. Brings up the 100 for the hosts.
Outside off, Azam offers no shot to this one.
Tossed up delivery on off, Shafiq drives it back towards the bowler.

The batsman has driven that ball straight back.

FOUR! Another fifty for Babar Azam. Jeez this guy is some player. He has looked so good out in the middle and he brings up his fifty in style. Short outside off, Babar transfers his weight on his back foot and then cuts it through point to get to his 13th Test fifty. Time to put it back to 12 and convert this into 4th Test ton?
FOUR! Not a welcome Vishwa would have wanted. Back of a length on off, Asad is quick to get on his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! Stumped! Karunaratne called Embuldeniya to provide him with the breakthrough and he has done just that. He has got the big fish here. Brilliant bowling this from Lasith. Gives this air on off, the ball turns and bounces away from Babar. Azam tries to come down the track and defend it but gets beaten. Dickwella behind the stumps does the rest as Babar was too far down the track. Maybe the break brought in a lapse of concentration here for the ever focused Babar.

Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Shafiq drives it through mid off for a single.

OUT! No bat and three reds! Pakistan lose both their reviews. No. 5 goes down on the stroke of Tea. Haris Sohail's struggle comes to an end. Pakistan in some trouble here. Embuldeniya tosses it up around off, Haris Sohail lunges forward and looks to defend but does not account for the turn. It spins back in sharply and brushes the front pad and then the back. A huge shout and up goes the finger. Sohail reviews just in the nick of time after having a chat with his partner. Time for the replays and it shows the on-field call is the right one.
FOUR! Ends the session with a boundary. Floated delivery on middle, Rizwan plays a sweep towards fine leg for a boundary and gets off the mark in style. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!

And Shafiq gets to his fifty as he gets a single on the very first ball of this session! On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one. He has held fort at one end and he needs to continue. Needs someone to support him though.

OUT! KABOOM! Right through the defense and Rizwan is knocked over. Sri Lanka continue from where they left off before the break. That is another excellent delivery. It lands just outside off and it is on a length. It jags back in sharply. Rizwan prods forward to defend but does so outside the line. The ball sneaks between the gap of bat and pad and hits the top of middle. Another one bites the dust and Sri Lanka into the bowling-all rounders now. Pakistan have a good chance to keep the hosts under 200.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front. What a delivery to bowl to the no. 8 batter. Too good for someone who does not have a big reputation with the bat. Extremely full and on off, Yasir Shah plants his front foot across, he looks to flick but misses and is trapped in front. Up goes the finger immediately as the Lankans start appealing. Kumara on a hat-trick. Asad Shafiq continues to watch wickets falling at the other end. Pakistan in big, big trouble now.
OHHH! top, top hat-trick delivery but equally well played. A very full ball and on off, Abbas jams it out nicely.

NOT OUT! That is a waste of a review to be honest! It is not only going down leg but also too high. Sri Lanka lose a review. This is shorter in length and on the pads. Abbas fails to put bat on ball and is hit high on the pads. Dickwella makes a huge appeal and Kumara joins in late. The umpire shakes his head. The keeper wants his captain to review and he does so. Replays show the on-field call is the right one. Dickwella probably got a little too excited with all the wickets falling. He needs to calm down a little as that never looked out.
A bumper to end! Abbas ducks under it. End of a brilliant over by Kumara. The Lankans could not have had a better start after the break. Just the run and two wickets from it.
Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq drives it to mid off.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Asad defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery on off, Shafiq cuts it towards point for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Abbas blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abbas defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abbas looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Full delivery outside off, Shafiq drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer, Shafiq does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on middle, Shafiq nudges it towards the leg side.
On a length and outside off, Shafiq pushes it towards covers for a run.
On a good length on off, Abbas defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on leg, Abbas looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Tosses it up on middle, defended.
One more floated delivery on middle, solidly blocked.
Angled on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
A full toss on off, it is hit down to long off for one.
OUT! CAUGHT! Embuldeniya gets his third wicket. Flighted delivery on middle, Abbas looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where Dhananjaya de Silva takes a good catch.
Tossed up delivery on off, Afridi defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
Short delivery outside off, Shafiq cuts it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq drives it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Asad blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it back towards the bowler.
Short delivery on middle, Shafiq pulls it through square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Asad keeps it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Asad flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Afridi tucks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! TAKEN! Lahiru Kumara has got the last recognized batter, the well set Asad Shafiq. His 4th wicket and Pakistan are nine down and there are still 15 more runs for them to get to 200. It is banged short and on the body, Asad looks to help it on its way but gets a top edge. It goes high in the air towards fine leg where Fernando runs in a little and takes it easily. 5 balls Kumara has in this over to get the fifer.
Full delivery on off, Naseem plays it towards covers for a single.
On a good length on off, Afridi plays it to point.
Full delivery on off, Afridi plays it towards mid off.
Short delivery outside off, Shaheen looks to cut but misses it.
Full delivery on middle, Afridi flicks it through square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Afridi defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Tossed up delivery on middle, Afridi plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's the end of a very timid show with the bat from Pakistan. Embuldeniya gets his fourth. Floated delivery on off, Afridi comes down the track and lofts it over mid off but does not get the timing on it. It goes towards Angelo Mathews who runs backwards from mid off and takes a good catch. From 127/3 PAKISTAN ARE ALL OUT FOR 191!
Action straightaway! Afridi starts with a full delivery on leg, Fernando looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.

FOUR LEG BYES! Sri Lanka are off the mark courtesy of some wild swing and delivery from Shaheen. Its pitched around leg Fernando looks to flick but the ball kisses his pads anf and goes away from the keeper down the leg side. Rizwan dives to his left but has no chance of stopping that from going to the fence.
On a good length on off, Fernando plays it to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Fernando drives it past the bowler through mid on. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Fernando plays it towards the off side for a run.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on leg, Oshada looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Karunaratne punches it to point.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Dimuth looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length on leg, Fernando looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes over first slip towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Karunaratne defends it out.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Dimuth looks to defend but misses it.
Outside off, Karunaratne offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Dimuth drives it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on middle, Fernando defends it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Oshada shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Fernando defends it out.
On a good length on off, Oshada defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Fernando looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Full delivery outside off, Karunaratne drives it through point for a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Karunaratne taps it to point.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Oshada flicks it through square leg for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Dimuth taps it to point.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller on off, Karunaratne keeps his balance and his head straight and plays a lovely looking straight drive for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Dimuth flicks it through square leg. Two runs taken.
Good length delivery outside off, Fernando looks to play at it but decides to leave it at the last moment.

OUT! Caught! Great use of the review from Pakistan. They knew there was an edge. They were adamant about it and the Ultra Edge is in agreement with them. Good bowling this but the route taken by Oshada is not the smartest one. Fuller outside off, Shaeen wants Oshada to go for the drive and Oshada falls in the trap. The ball goes past the outside edge and straight into the gloves of Rizwan. He is up and cheering. The fielders from slip cordon are also sure that they have their man. They look at the umpire but he is unmoved. They take it upstairs. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows a spike as the ball goes past the bat.
On off, Mendis starts his innings with a good, solid front foot defense.
Good length ball on middle and off, Mendis looks to block with a slant bat but the ball moves in and hits the pads off the inside edge.
Way wide outside off, Mendis is not interested.
Full on off, KM pushes it to mid off to get through the over. A very good over from Shaheen. Has provided the hosts with the early breakthrough they were looking for.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne defends it to covers.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but misses it.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but misses it.
On a length on middle, Dimuth flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, Mendis lets it go.
On a good length on leg, Karunaratne looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Length delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through square leg for a run.
Bowls it wide outside off, Mendis lets it go.
Short of a length delivery, Mendis pulls it over mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Kusal shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Classic shot. Full delivery outside off, Karunaratne drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Dimuth looks to defend but misses it.
Outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Karunaratne taps it to point.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on middle, Mendis flicks it through square leg for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne plays it to point.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Karunaratne drives it to mid off.
Outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, Mendis flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Bowls a bouncer, Dimuth does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Dimuth keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on middle, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Dimuth offers no shot to this one.

OUT! Chops it on! Abbas strikes! The Lankan captain departs, a big wicket as Karunaratne is capable of playing long innings. A poor shot this to be honest! This is shorter and just outside off, not enough room to play this shot. Karunaratne still looks to cut but gets a bottom edge which shatters the stumps behind. He trudges off slowly as the Pakistan players celebrate. They need to keep picking wickets at regular intervals. Sri Lanka trail by 152.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! On a good length on off, Mathews looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
A good short one but it is spotted early. Mendis evades it.
The bowler goes wide of the crease and it is angled into the middle pole, blocked.
Wristy! On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Very full and on middle, Mathews pushes it to mid off for one.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
Three! A little too straight, Mendis looks to flick it through mid-wicket. The bat turns in his hand as he connects with the ball. Still gets three. Fifty up for the Lankans.
On middle, defended nicely.
On off, it straightens a touch. Mendis looks to work it on the leg side with the angle but ends up getting a soft leading edge towards mid off.
Outside off, not played at.
Another one on middle, Mendis keeps it out nicely.
That is a beauty! This is starts on off which means the batter has to play at it. Mendis looks to defend, the ball moves away and beats the outside edge.
Gets this one to angle into the batter, blocked.
FIVE WIDES! Bowls a bouncer down the leg side, Mathews ducks under it. It goes past Dickwella towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Mathews offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Angelo flicks it through square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
On a length on middle, Mendis flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Outside off, Mathews lets it go.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Kusal Mendis! Short and outside off, Mendis cuts it over point for a boundary.

OUT! That is clean as a whistle! Mendis is out of here. Another stand which had started to build has been cut short. Exactly what Pakistan want, they need to keep picking wickets at regular intervals. Abbas is the breakthrough provider once again. He is rewarded for the second time to keep hitting the right lines and lengths. This is on a length again and on off, Mendis lunges forward to play the original trajectory but the ball moves away. Kisses the outside edge and goes low towards first slip where Sohail pouches it. The Pakistan players start celebrating but Mendis stands his ground. Umpires have a chat and then take it upstairs. SOFT SIGNAL IS OUT! Replays also suggest it is a clean catch. Can Pakistan take at least another before Stumps?

On a good length on leg, Embuldeniya looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It lobs to short leg where he appeals for the catch but the umpire shakes his head. Replays show that it came off the pad.
Bowls a bouncer, Embuldeniya lets it sail through to the keeper.
Outside off, Lasith shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Embuldeniya looks to defend but misses it.
On a length on middle, Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Mathews offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on middle, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and outside off, Mathews looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Lasith looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on middle, Embuldeniya defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Lasith looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards slips on one bounce.
On a good length on off, Embuldeniya blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Embuldeniya lets it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Embuldeniya drives it uppishly through mid off. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Naseem starts with a good length ball way outside off. Embuldeniya is happy to watch it go to the keeper. No movement in the first ball.
No Ball! Naseem is guilty of overstepping and Sri Lanka have the first run of the day. Length ball outside off and Embuldeniya is not interested in it.
Comes wide of the crease and uses the angle to make it come in from outside off. Embuldeniya tries to get the feel of the ball on his bat but misses.
Fuller and closer to the off pole. Embuldeniya looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes off the outer half of his bat to the right of gully. The fielder there dives and saves runs for his side.
Short ball. It is around off, Embuldeniya sways away from it.
Smart bowling. After going short he goes full on the stumps. Embuldeniya though is ready for it and defends it.
Just a no ball off the first one. Back of a length outside off, Lasith sways away from it and gets through the first over unscathed.
Abbas starts on the corridor of off stump. Mathews looks to defend it but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards gully.

Wild slash at it but Mathews misses. Good lenth ball outside off. Mathews sees it is short and outside off so he looks to cut it but misses. He would have been gutted with himself had he nicked that to the keeper.
On a length on middle and leg. This one sticks on the pitch and comes to Mathews. He manages to block it.
Slightly shorter on middle and leg, Angelo blocks it off his back foot.
Abbas continues to target the middle and leg stump. This is slightly fuller and Mathews is forced to defend it off his front foot.
Back of a length around off, Mathews blocks it to get through Abbas' first over of the day.
First runs off the bat for the day. Fuller on off, Embuldeniya strokes it through covers and gets a couple.
Good length ball around off, Embuldeniya intentionally plays it wide of gully and gets a couple as Masood cleans it before the ropes.

FOUR! How lucky is Embuldeniya! Good length ball which jags back in from around off. Lasith looks to defend but gets an inside edge. The ball hits the top of off but the bails refuse to be dislodged. The ball goes to the right of Rizwan and he dives but cannot hold onto it. The ball then races away to the fence. Unlucky is the word for Pakistan.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

Dropeed! Babar has put down a sitter here. Good bowling from young Naseem and he should have had Embuldeniya. Good length ball on off, Lasith looks to defend it away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of gully. Babar there takes it too casually and the ball pops out of his hand. Unlucky is the only word one can associate with Naseem at this point in time.
End of an eventful over. Should have had Embuldeniya back but he is still out there. Back of a length on off, LE defends it off his back foot.
Around off, Mathews blocks it off his back foot.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Fuller on the stumps, Mathews blocks it.
Outside off, AM does not disturb that.
Beauty! Good length ball pitching on off. Mathews looks to defend it but the ball fizzles away and squares Angelo all ends up.
On the pads, Mathews glances it to mid-wicket.
Good bowling. Pacy and on a length just outside off, Embuldeniya looks to defend but misses it all ends up.
This time manages to get bat on ball. Naseem goes full and on the stumps, Lasith manages to get hgis bat down and block it.
Fuller on off, LE blocks it with relative ease.
Bouncer! Good contest this between the two. Naseem bangs it in short and Embuldeniya sways away from it.
Good length ball around off, Embuldeniya drives it through covers and gets a couple.
Beaten! Goes wide of the crease and makes the ball come in with the angle from well outside off. Embuldeniya looks to defend but once again the ball just about misses the outside edge of his bat.
Fuller on off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Length ball outside off, Mathews leaves it alone.

Shorter around off, Mathews walks towards it and then glances it through mid-wicket and runs the first one hard. He wants the second but Embuldeniya is hesitant. He later goes for it, the fielder sends the throw at the bowler's end away from the stumps. Abbas collects it and hits the direct hit with an underarm throw. Lasith though puts in a dive which takes him home comfortably.
Fuller on off, Mathews pushes it towards mid on and gets to the other end.
Full on off, Embuldeniya defends it off the front foot.
Embuldeniya shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot to get through the over.
Outside off, Mathews leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Mathews punches it to cover.
Full on off, Angelo defends it with a straight bat.
Good, solid front foot defense now. Full on off, Mathews defends it to the left of Naseem.

This one jags back in a bit. Good length ball around off, it comes in off the deck. Mathews looks to punch but it goes to the leg side off the inner half of his bat. Smart bowling this from Naseem. He is bowling it straight to him and not offering much width to play with as he likes to cut and pull.
Now Naseem offers width to Angelo outside off but his cuts is straight to the man at point.
Abbas with a bouncer now! It is a well directed one as well. Around the body, Embuldeniya manages to gets his head away from it.
Another short ball. How rarely have we seen Abbas bowl short? He has done it back-to-back here. It is around the boddy. Embuldeniya ducks and takes one hand off the bat and looks to flick but misses.

OUT! Caught! This is some very weird way to get out. No one can actually understand what Embuldeniya was thinking. This is a bizarre way to get out. The two bouncers went on Embuldeniya's nerves. So now he looks to play a slog sweep, yes a slog sweep. It is fuller on middle, Embuldeniya is a bit early in his premeditated slog sweep and ends up getting a thick outside edge. It goes straight to the man at second slip. This time Embuldeniya is not lucky as Asad Shafiq takes an easy catch. The night watchman's adventures comes to an end.
Good length ball on off, Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Dinesh defends it to point and shouts a loud no.
End of an excellent over from Abbas. Wicket maiden. The last ball is another one which he pegs on the off stump. Chandimal defends it towards cover and gets through the over.
Shaheen starts with a lenght ball down the leg side. Mathews looks to flick it but misses.
Better ball. Back of a length ball on off. This shoots up onto the batter. Mathews looks to defend and does so off the upper half of his bat.
Full on off, Mathews strokes it towards mid on and gets to the other end.
Around off, Chandimal blocks it off the front foot.
Good length ball on top of middle and off. It comes back in a bit. Chandimal looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his thigh pad.
Outside off, DC leaves it alone to see off Shaheen's first of the day.
Good length delivery around off, Mathews defends it towards mid on.
On a length on middle, Mathews flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal defends it towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Chandimal defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Dinesh defends it off the front foot.

OUT! Caught! Sri Lanka have half their side back in the hut. Brilliant ball this from Shaheen. He is a very talented bowler and this ball just shows how good he is. Good length ball around off, Shaheen makes the ball nip back in. Mathews looks to defend but is completely outdone by the inward movement. It kisses the inside edge and goes to the keeper. Rizwan takes an easy catch. Shaheen is pumping the air in joy. Both the overnight batsmen are back in the hut and Pakistan on a roll here. SL trail by 111.
Good length ball outside off, Dhananjaya looks to defend but gets beaten as this one shapes away. Very good bowling this from Shaheen.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya defends it with a dead bat.
Outside off, Dhananjaya is not interested to play at that.
Fuller on off, Dhananjaya pushes it to cover.
On the fourth stump line, Dhananjaya lets it go.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Dinesh keeps it out.
Bowls a bouncer, Chandimal sways away from it.
Length delivery on off, Chandimal taps it through covers for a run.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
On a length on off, Chandimal plays it to covers.
Outside off, Chandimal offers no shot to this one.
Again outside off, Chandimal shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Dinesh looks to cut but misses it.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and just outside off, Chandimal looks to defend but misses it.

FOUR! Aerial but still a good shot. Chandimal sees width outside off, he slashes at it. It goes uppishly through the vacant backward point region for a boundary. Much needed boundary for the tourists.
On a length on leg, Dhananjaya looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen take a single. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
On a good length on off, Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dinesh defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Full delivery outside off, Chandimal drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
On a length on middle, Dhananjaya nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya defends it out.
On a good length on off, de Silva blocks it off the back foot.

Full delivery outside off, Dhananjaya looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man where Yasir Shah chases the ball, slides and does well to stop it before the ropes. He picks the ball and throws it to Babar Azam. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya blocks it well.
Full delivery on middle, de Silva drives it to mid on.
Short delivery on off, Chandimal makes room and cuts it through point for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, de Silva makes room and slaps it through covers for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Chandimal blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Chandimal keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dinesh offers a forward defense on this one.
On a good length on off, de Silva defends it out.
Bowls a well-directed bouncer on middle, Dhananjaya looks to pull but gets a top edge. It lands safely towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dinesh defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Chandimal offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Chandimal looks to flick but misses it.
Flighted delivery on middle, de Silva flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dhananjaya drives it through mid off for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Chandimal defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Chandimal cuts it through point for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Dhananjaya comes down the track and blocks it.
Loopy delivery on off, de Silva pushes it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya drives it straight past the bowler through mid off. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot.
On a length on middle, Dhananjaya pushes it through mid on for a single.
FOUR! That missed the leg stump by a whisker. On a good length on middle, Chandimal looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It misses the leg stump and goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Dinesh defends it off the front foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Chandimal does well to duck under it.
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery on off, Chandimal looks to cut but misses it. It goes towards the keeper who fails to collect the ball.
Flighted delivery on off, Dhananjaya plays it to point.
Loopy delivery on off, de Silva punches it through point for a single.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it through mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, de Silva blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Chandimal defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Chandimal does well to duck under it.
Short of a length delivery on leg, Chandimal looks to pull but misses it.
On a length on middle, Dinesh flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.
Good length delivery on off, de Silva defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, de Silva cuts it through point for a single.
FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Dhananjaya pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, de Silva drives it to covers.
Floated delivery on middle, de Silva looks to cut but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flighted delivery on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Dinesh blocks it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, de Silva punches it through point for a run.
Bowls a bouncer, Chandimal ducks under it.
Bowls a bumper outside off, Chandimal lets it sail through to the keeper.
NO BALL! Naseem Shah oversteps! Outside off, Chandimal leaves it alone.
Length delivery outside off, Chandimal taps it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
On a length on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Short delivery on middle, de Silva pulls it through square leg where the fielder does well to stop it with a dive. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dhananjaya plays it to point.
SIX! Amazing shot. Flighted delivery on off, de Silva comes down the track and lofts it over long off for a biggie.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region.
Floated delivery on middle, de Silva defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Easily and nicely played! Shorter around off, Dhananjaya gets on his back foot and punches it through covers for a boundary. Dhananjaya is once again looking good here.

Much better from Yasir! Gives this one air and also pitches it up. Dhananjaya lunges forward to defend but the ball spins away from him. This is what is required from Yasir. He just needs to keep things simple here.
Outside off, Chandimal shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal drives it to mid on.
Length delivery on off, Dinesh plays it to point.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Excellently played! Good length ball around off, Chandimal waits for it and then punches it with ease and grace through wide of mid off for a boundary.
Outside off, Dinesh lets it go.
Flighted delivery on off, Dhananjaya drives it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to mid off.
Floated delivery on off, Dinesh plays it towards covers for a run.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Silva defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Dhananjaya drives it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal blocks it well.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it towards mid-wicket where Babar Azam misfields and concedes a single.
On a length on middle, Dhananjaya flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, de Silva blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dinesh punches it through point. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Floated delivery on middle, Dinesh tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Dinesh drives it towards mid on.
Loopy delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to mid off.
Floated delivery on off, Dinesh drives it towards mid off.
On a good length on middle, de Silva defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Dhananjaya drives it through mid on. The batsmen get two runs.

OUT! Caught! Big wicket for Pakistan! It's the man in form, the man who had a century in the previous game and the man who was looking very good out in the middle, Dhananjaya de Silva. Shaheen strikes again in his spell. It is the short ball that has done the trick for the hosts. A very well directed bouncer from Shaheen, it is on the body and catches Dhananjaya de Silva by surprise. He is hurried into the pull and ends up top edging it to the right of fine leg. Abbas comes running in and takes a very good catch. Shaheen brings out his trademark celebration. One has to credit Mohammad Rizwan as well as before this delivery was bowled it was he who suggested Shaheen to bang it in short. So excellent work from the keeper as well. As they say that bowler and keeper's have a special partnership. The 67-run stand is broken and Sri Lanka still trail by 44 runs.
Outside off, Dickwella does not bother to play at that.
BEATEN! Good shape on this one. On a good length and outside off, Dickwella looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Niroshan defends it off the back foot.
Leg spinner around the pads, Chandimal glances it against the spin towards square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Dickwella defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Dickwella gets down and sweeps it to the right of backward square leg. The fielder there dives on that side and saves runs for his side.
Yasir goes short around off, Dickwella defends it calmly.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella blocks it.
FOUR BYES! That's missed everything. Floated outside off, Dickwella looks to paddle it but he misses. The ball goes past the keeper and first slip and to the fence.
FOUR! Smart cricket. Back of a length outside off, Chandimal sees that there is no one at deep third man so he plays the upper cut with ease and fetches himself a boundary.

Beauty! There is a lot of appeal from the bowler and the fielders but Rizwan did not go up at all. There was a sound but it was of the ball hitting the thigh pad. Gem of a delivery this. Good length ball pitching on off. It jags back in viciously. Dinesh looks to defend but the ball goes right through the gate of pad and bat. It clips something on its way to the keeper. Shaheen is convinced that kiss came of the bat but Rizwan does not go up and the umpire agrees with Rizwan. They think about the review but opt against it. Good decision as replays later on confirm that the ball kissed the thigh pad. Very good decision from Bruce Oxenford.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Chandimal tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Niroshan keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Chandimal flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dickwella flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Floated delivery on off, Dinesh defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Chandimal blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Chandimal plays it towards covers for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dickwella plays it to point.
Outside off, Dinesh lets it go.
Again outside off, Dinesh shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Chandimal flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
EDGE AND FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes between second slip and gully towards third man for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a length on off, Dickwella guides it towards third man for a boundary.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Dickwella looks to play a scoop shot but misses it.
On a good length on off, Chandimal defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Dinesh looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a good length on middle, Dinesh defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Chandimal keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Dinesh plays it to point.
On a good length on middle, Dinesh defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Dickwella shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Dickwella flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Chandimal blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Dinesh blocks it well.
Full delivery on middle, Chandimal drives it back towards the bowler.
Full again on off, Dinesh drives it to covers.
On a good length on middle, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Niroshan keeps it out.
On a length on middle, Dickwella nudges it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery outside off, Dickwella taps it to point.
Outside off, Dickwella offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Dickwella blocks it off the back foot. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Absolute jaffa to start the session. Good length ball on off and middle, it jags back in and dissects Chandimal in half. He is a lucky man not to get any bat on it on its way to the keeper.
First run off the session and it has come off the inside edge. Full on off and middle, Chandimal looks to drive but the ball goes off the inside edge behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller on middle, Dickwella flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
First ball that is away from the stumps and Dickwella shoulders arms to it.
Length delivery on off, Niroshan defends it by getting right behind the line of the ball.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! Poor from the Pakistani fielder. Slightly fuller outside off, Dickwella nudges it towards point and calls for a quick single. Chandimal responds and the fielder from gully quickly gets to the ball and has a shy at the keeper's end. He misses and there is no one backing up so the ball goes away to the fence.
On a good length on off, Dickwella defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Dickwella drives it to covers.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Dickwella looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Niroshan taps it to point.
FOUR! Don't bother running that was four the moment it left the bat. Good length ball outside off. Dickwella lunges forward and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Now calmly defends it this ball to get through the over. Simple and smart cricket this from the Sri Lankan wicket keeper batsman.
On a good length on middle, Chandimal looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full delivery on off, Dinesh drives it towards mid off.
On a good length and outside off, Chandimal punches it to point.
Outside off, Dinesh shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to mid off.
Short delivery on middle, Dinesh pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Chandimal looks to drive but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Chandimal defends it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Chandimal drives it to covers.
Short and outside off, Dinesh slaps it towards covers for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Dickwella looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.

OUT! Bowled! Abbas you beauty! His teammates are all over him and no wonder why. He has bowled a cracker of a delivery. You might look at him and say he has no pace at all but boy this man can do some magic with it. Seam up delivery pitching outside off. Dickwella looks to defend it with a straight bat but the ball zips in and hits the top of off. Every pacer likes to hit the top of the stumps and he has hit just that. Too good! His 4th wicket of the game and he is up in joy. The trail is now 7 but they have just three wickets remaining.
Shaheen starts with a good length ball on middle, it is defended.

Huge appeal for LBW! A massive one! Pakistan do not opt for the review. Brilliant ball this one. It pitches on middle and then swings in a bit. Chandimal looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Shaheen appeals, he continues appealing. Nothing from the umpire. The skipper comes around but eventually opts against the review.
Around off, pushed to mid off.

Another huge appeal but probably an inside edge on this one. Pitches around off and middle, Chandimal flicks but gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal but it dies down quickly, probably because they realized the inside edge on this one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and the pads, Chandimal flicks but once again misses to get hit on the pads. No appeal this time as it was clearly going down leg.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Abbas. On a good length and outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
Play and a miss! Good length delivery outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
On a length around off, pushed towards cover.
Length and on off this one, Perera pushes it towards mid on.
Good length ball around off, it is defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Fuller and just outside off, Chandimal drives it straight to mid off.
Fuller and on off this time, Chandimal comes forward and pushes it to mid off again.
Full and on off, blocked coming forward by Dinesh.
Fuller around off, Chandimal drives again, this time the ball goes to mid-wicket off the inner half of the bat for a run.
Good length ball on middle, Perera tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, tapped towards point for a single.
Bouncer and around off, Perera ducks under it.
Shortish around off, Perera punches it to mid off.
Full and on off, stroked towards mid off.
Shortish around off, Perera taps it towards cover-point where Masood dives and saves runs. A single for Perera though.
Well fielded! This time it is Abid Ali in the covers. A full ball just outside off, Chandimal drives it towards cover where Abid dives and stops the ball.
On a length around off, Chandimal blocks it back to the bowler.
Good shot! Fuller outside off, Dilruwan drives it through point and gets a couple as Shan Masood stops it with a slide before the ropes. The trail now stands at just 2.
Good length delivery on off, Perera defends it nicely.
Very full around off. Dilruwan does well to get his bat down and block it.
On the pads, Perera flicks it through square leg and gets a brace. Scores level now.
On the stumps, Dilruwan defends it off the front foot.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

FOUR! Sri Lanka are into the lead and Chandimal gets to his half ton. His 18th in Tests. Gets there with a beautiful drive off the back foot. Slightly short ball around off, Chandimal stands tall and punches it through the cover region for a boundary. Brilliant innings this one. He is making the opportunity count after getting out to a peach of a delivery in the first game. Can he consolidate the lead for the visitors?
Around off, it is defended.
Shortish and on off, pushed to mid off.
Shortish and outside off, Chandimal stands tall and defends it to mid off.
Full and on middle, Chandimal clips it between mid-wicket and mid on and picks a couple of runs.
Shortish ball outside off, defended back to the bowler.
FOUR! Going for the yorker but instead dishes out a full toss ball outside off, Perera drives it through point nicely to bag his first boundary of his innings. 200 up for the hosts.
Fuller and on off, stroked to mid off.
Full and outside off, once again it is pushed towards mid off.
Outside off, Perera lets it be. As the ball goes behind, it dies down in front of Rizwan who cannot pouch it cleanly.
Ouch! That looks nasty! A skiddy bouncer on middle. Perera looks to duck but gets his eyes off the ball. It hits him flush on the grill. He takes off the helmet. Time for the concussion test.
On a good length and outside off, Perera looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on middle, Chandimal defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dinesh plays it to point.
FOUR! That is hammered! Floated delivery outside off, Chandimal drives it through covers for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Dinesh punches it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Chandimal blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Chandimal keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Perera drives it to mid off.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Perera lets it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Perera drives it through point for a run.
Outside off, Chandimal does not bother to play at that.
Short of a length delivery, Chandimal pulls it uppishly towards mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Short again and outside off, Chandimal cuts it through point for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dinesh drives it to mid on.
Tossed up delivery on off, Chandimal drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on middle, Perera blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Dilruwan looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards the off side.
FOUR! Good shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Perera lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off, Perera defends it off the front foot.
Around off on a good length, it is defended back to the bowler.
FOUR! Hammered! What a shot! Short ball on middle, Chandimal swivels and smashes the pull into the deep square leg fence.
Full on middle, flicked to mid on.
Around off, it is defended towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over! Shortish ball outside off, Chandimal comes forward and taps it through covers beautifully. The ball races to the fence.
FOUR! Another one! Chandimal is taking the attack to the opposition. Another shortish length outside off, Chandimal punches it off the back foot past the diving cover fielder and into the fence.
Fuller on on middle, Perera defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one around off, Perera looks to defend but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and goes towards point uppishly. A single.
Flighted and fuller around off, Dinesh eases it through mid off for a single.
Full and on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Flighted and around off, blocked.
Fuller and down the leg side. Perera looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the pads and goes towards short fine leg for a leg bye.
Quicker one and outside off, pushed to long off for a single.
Another flatter one outside off, tapped towards point by Chandimal.
Floated around off on a fuller length, defended towards covers.
Full and outside off, Chandimal drives it well but finds short extra cover.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball around off, pushed towards the extra cover fielder once again.
Fuller one on the pads, Perera flicks but misses to get hit on the pad. It hits the pad and goes towards square leg for a leg bye.
Short around off, stroked straight to cover.
Full and around off, Perera strokes to long off for a single. 50-run stand is up between the two.
The batsman works it down the leg side. They pick up a single.

OUT! Caught! The part-timer strikes. Not the perfect ball at all but he has got the massive wicket of Chandimal. Short and just outside off, Dinesh goes for the cut. He ends up slicing it towards Shan Masood at backward point who makes no mistake. End of a very good knock from Chandimal. He could've swelled the lead to a bigger one, so a very important wicket this one.
Flighted around off, Vishwa looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The short leg fielder pouches the ball and appeals but nothing from the umpire.
Tossed up delivery on off, Dilruwan defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Perera looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip on one bounce.
Floated delivery on middle, Perera flicks it towards square leg for a run.

NOT OUT! That bounced just in front of Shafiq's hand. So, the third umpire has changed the soft signal, which means he was sure, absolutely sure. Took a lot of time but eventually gave the benefit of doubt to the Lankan batter. It was a flighted ball just outside off, Fernando drives but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to Shafiq at first slip. He catches and celebrates. The umpire is not sure though as they refer it upstairs. The third umpire checks with various angles and then eventually finds it bouncing just in front of the fingers. So, Fernando survives.
Around off and middle, it is defended towards mid-wicket.
Flighted around off, blocked off the back foot.
SIX! This is out of here. Someone please give the ball back. Floated on the stumps, Dilruwan comes down the track and smokes it over the bowler's head for a biggie. The lead now over 50!
Short delivery on off, Perera cuts it to point.
Flighted delivery on middle, Perera defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Perera drives it towards mid off for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Fernando blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Vishwa defends it off the front foot.
Bouncer to start the new spell. Perera ducks under it.
Shortish length outside off, Perera taps it through point. It goes towards sweeper cover but he denies a single. Looking for quick runs while farming the strike?
FOUR! Flicked nicely! Full and on the pads, Perera flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets which means Perera survives to continue swelling the Lankan lead. Let's talk about the ball. It is a shortish length just outside off, Perera looks to defend it off the back foot but misses to get hit on the pads. The bowler and the slip cordon appeals but not out says the umpire. Shaheen though is sure as he asks the skipper to go for the DRS. And he then eventually himself signals it to the umpire. Let's see what the replays show. The front foot is okay. Time for Ultra Edge, nothing on it. Ball Tracker time. Here it comes, It is just clipping the bails of off and middle. Umpire's call it will be then, on hitting the stumps. So, Perera stays. Pakistan keep their review.

Fuller and outside off, Perera drives but gets an under edge which both first slip and the wicket keeper cannot collect. It goes between them just outside the ring. The batters take off the single. The first slip fielder gets to the ball and aims a throw at the striker's end but misses. Had he hit, Fernando would've been gone.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a length on middle, Perera flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Dilruwan defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Perera drives it uppishly towards mid on but does not take the single.
On a length on off, Perera taps it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Bowls a bouncer, Fernando does well to duck under it.
On a good length on off, Vishwa keeps it out.
NO BALL! Afridi oversteps! Bowls a bouncer, Perera does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on off, Perera taps it to point.
Full delivery on middle, Perera drives it through mid on but does not take the single.
Length delivery on middle, Perera defends it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
On a good length on off, Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Vishwa does well to dig it out.
On a good length on middle, Fernando blocks it off the back foot. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Short and outside off, Perera punches it through cover-point. Single denied  as there is protection in the deep.
Shortish around off, pushed towards point.
On the pads this time, Perera tucks it towards fine leg and looks for a single first but later decides against it.
FOUR! Poor line and punished! A full ball down the leg side, Dilruwan clips it to the fine leg fence nicely.
On middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Full and on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Shaheen starts with a ball around off, it is blocked.
Full and on middle this time, Vishwa digs it out nicely.
Fuller and around off, Fernando blocks it nicely once again.
Bouncer! Shortish ball outside off, Vishwa does well but sways away.
Bouncer again! Another bumper which is aimed at the head. Vishwa, somehow manages to sway away. Lucky not to get hit. Could've been very risky as he took his eyes off the ball.
On off and on a fuller length ball. It is defended.
Good length ball on middle, Perera looks to flick but misses. A stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Short ball outside off, Perera cuts but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and around off, Perera flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and calls for a couple. However, Fernando was slow to take off for the first run so just a single.
Good length ball outside off, Vishwa guides it through gully for a single.
Fuller and on middle, it is defended.

NOT OUT! No bat! A review lost for Pakistan. Shortish length ball down the leg side. Perera looks to flick but misses. Rizwan behind the wicket pouches the ball and appeals instantly. The umpire is not interested. Rizwan is sure though that there was some noise. He convinces his skipper and they go for the DRS. Let's see what the replays confirm. First, the front foot, it is fine. Ultra Edge time, flat line, it is as it passes the bat. Then a line appears, it is of the ball kissing the thigh pad. One review done and dusted for the hosts.
Full delivery on middle, Fernando defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Vishwa defends it out.
Good length delivery on leg, Fernando looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Full delivery outside off, Fernando drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Bowls it down the leg side, Perera looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Dilruwan blocks it off the front foot.
On middle, Vishwa tucks it towards square leg off the back foot.

Dropped! A tough chance though this one for the skipper!  A slower one outside off, Fernando just checks his shot towards covers. The ball goes towards Azhar at extra cover who throws his left hand to catch but it just does not stick. It goes behind and a single taken.
Shortish around off, Perera cuts but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Play and a miss! Another good length ball outside off, Perera throws his bat to get beaten.
On the pads on a fullish length, Perera flicks but makes no connection. It goes towards mid-wicket and they take a leg bye.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Bouncer on middle! Dilruwan ducks under it.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! Guided it nicely! Poor line from Shaheen. It is on the pads, Perera just clips it to the fine leg fence and moves to 44.

FOUR! Now down the ground! Slightly overpitched around off, Dilruwan this time gets on top of the bounce and creams it through mid on. Afridi tries to get his hand down but could not get it. Perera moves to 48.
Bouncer! Perera ducks it away.
Shortish on middle, Perera taps it towards backward point and thinks for a single. Perera though it not interested.
Hit wicket? No, just safe! That was a bouncer which did not rise enough. Fernando tried to duck under it but fell in the process. Does well to keep himself away from the stumps at the very end.
Another bouncer! Fernando sways away from it nicely. Called wide.
Another one! It is outside off, Fernando has no problems ducking under it.
Sprays down the leg side this time. Fernando lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish length around off, it is blocked off the back foot.
Landed on middle, it is worked towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Vishwa tucks it towards mid-wicket to see off the over.
Beaten! Beautifully bowled! It is slightly shortish around off, it then comes in and cuts Perera into half. Lucky not to get an inside edge on that one.
Fuller around off, driven to mid off.

OUT! LBW! The review will not help Perera. He misses out on a well deserved half ton. Afridi bowls a pacy ball around middle and leg, Dilruwan looks to flick but he is early into the shot. It hits him flush on the pads and Afridi makes a loud appeal. The umpire raises the finger instantly. Perera too signals the 'T' without taking any time. Can the DRS save him? Let's find out. Front foot is okay. No willow, confirms the Ultra Edge. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Pitching in line. Hitting the wickets? No, but it is clipping the wickets, which means umpire's call stays and Perera has to depart for 48. A top innings though from him to help Pakistan take a good lead.
Fuller one on middle, Kumara keeps it out.

OUT! Timber! Five-fer for Afridi as he hits the top of off, first one in Tests for Shaheen. Kumara cannot add anything to the lead. Good length ball on off, Kumara looks to defend coming forward but misses the line of the ball. It goes behind and hits the top of off. That will be end of the Lankan innings.
Vishwa starts with a ball down the leg side. Masood goes for the flick but does not connect.
Gets the line right and dishes it out around off on a fuller length. Masood comes forward and blocks.
Wants to get off the mark but Abid sends him back. A shortish length around off, Masood taps it towards point and thinks for a single but Ali sends back, rightly so, as there was no run.
He is off the mark, so are Pakistan in the second innings. A ball on the pads, Masood works it towards fine leg for a single.
Abid gets off the mark too. Length ball on the pads, Abid tucks it to fine leg and takes a run.
Full and on off, Shan keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Abid lets it be.
Fuller and outside off. Ali comes on the front foot and drives. But the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the first slip on the bounce.
On the pads on a good length, Ali clips it wide of the fine leg fielder and scampers back for the second.
On the pads again, Ali once again hops and guides it to fine leg for a single.
Another ball on the pads, this is on the left-handers pad. Shan works it towards deep square leg for a run.
