FOUR! Beautifully driven! Slightly overpitched from Kumara, Ali leans into the drive and drives it to the long off fence. The fielder from the same position chases the ball down but the ball wins the race.
Full and around off, pushed to point.
Landed on middle and leg, tucked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely clipped! Shortish length ball on middle, Shan hops and tickles it fine to the fine leg fence. First boundary for Shan. This will give him a lot of confidence.
Landed around off, pushed to covers.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Good length ball around off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR LEG BYES! On the pads again, Ali looks to flick but gets hit high on the thigh pad. The ball though races to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball around off, Abid looks to defend but the ball goes to mid-wicket off the inner half of the bat for a single.
Around off, tapped towards cover for a single.
Overpitched and outside off, Ali drives it through covers sweetly. Three runs taken before the fielder can chase down the ball.
Back of a length ball on middle, Shan does well to sway away from it.
Full one on middle, Masood looks to flick but the ball takes the outer half of the bat goes through cover-point. A couple before the fielder can return the ball to the keeper. 11 from the over.

Brilliant stop! Dhananjaya de Silva it is. A short ball outside off, Abid cuts it off the back foot but de Silva flies to his right and makes a fine stop. A single taken though as the ball rolled just away from him.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball on middle, Shan tucks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads again, Shan works it towards mid-wicket for a quick single.

Huge appeal for LBW but not out says the umpire. Looks to be going over the stumps. Just behind good length, Ali looks to flick but makes no connection. The bowler and the slip cordon makes a loud appeal. The umpire shows no interest. The Lankans do not go for the review. A good call from them as the replays later on confirm that it was going over the stumps.
FOUR! Poor ball this one and Ali finds the fence. Good length ball on the pads of Ali. He nudges it to the fine leg fence.
Flighted delivery on off, Masood drives it towards mid on.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Masood drives it through mid on for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Abid offers no shot to this one.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
On off, Abid keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On a length around off, tapped to mid on.
Slash and a miss! A short ball outside off, Shan looks to cut but connects with air only.
Around off on a good length, Shan taps it towards point.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ali drives it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Floated delivery on middle, Abid plays a sweep through mid-wicket for a boundary.
BEATEN! Loopy delivery outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Masood offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Masood drives it towards mid on where the fielder tries to stop it but it goes through him. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Good length delivery on middle, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Sri Lanka does not lose the review though. Coming to the ball, it is a fuller ball on around off and middle, Masood looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the pads and the Lankans appeal. The umpire says no interest. Karunaratne after consulting the keeper and the bowler opts for the review. Here comes the replays. No bat involvement confirms the Ultra Edge. Here comes the Ball Tracker, pitched outside off and just clipping the leg stump. So, Masood survives. But a very good review from the Sri Lankans as had the umpire raised his finger, Masood would've been on his way.
Full ball around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ali keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Ali looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Ali nudges it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.

Flighted delivery on off, Masood drives it towards point where the fielder picks the ball and goes for a direct hit at the keeper's end but misses it. The throw was so fast that it goes as overthrows towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Masood punches it towards point for a run.
Short delivery on middle, Ali pulls it towards short leg where Kusal Mendis tries to take the catch but gets hit in the stomach.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid defends it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
On off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery and outside off, Abid cuts it through point for a single.
FOUR! Good shot. Flighted delivery on off, Masood punches it through point for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Masood defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Masood flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.
Full delivery on middle, Abid drives it straight where the ball hits Shan Masood's bat and goes towards mid off.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ali flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
On a good length and outside off, Abid shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Length delivery outside off, Ali punches it through covers for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Ali flicks it towards mid on for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Shan taps it towards point and makes a loud call of no for the single.
Beaten! Ripper this one. It pitches around off on a good length and goes straight past the outside edge of Shan's defensive poke.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Short delivery on off, Abid makes room and cuts it through point for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Masood punches it through point for a run.
Outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Abid keeps it out.
Short delivery outside off, Abid makes room and cuts it through point. The batsmen take a single.
Run straightaway to begin the day. Vishwa bowls a warm up delivery on the pads. Abid glances it towards square leg and gets a single to score the first run of the day.
Right on queue. Little bit of away shape on this one. Comes around the wicket and bowls it outside off, it moves away from the southpaw. Masood is cautious and does not offer any shot to it.

Shan gets his first runs of the day as well. Good length ball outside off, Shan dabs it to the left of gully. The fielder there dives and gets his hands to it but cannot stop it cleanly. The ball goes behind him and they take a couple.
Play and miss! Length ball outside off, Masood looks to make the most of the width on offer and tries to cut it away but misses.

Beauty! Absolute peach this from Vishwa. A similar delivery which got the better of Masood in the first innings. The only difference is this one was outside off. On the fourth stump line. Shan looks to defend but the ball zips away and squares him all ends up. There is a noise as the ball goes straiight to the keeper. Vishwa is confident but Dickwella does not go up. The umpire also shakes it away. Sri Lanka opt against the review and rightfully so as the sound was of the bat clipping the pad and not the ball kissing the bat.
Good end to the over. Slightly fuller on off and middle, it comes back in. Shan looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball goes towards point. Nervy start for Masood.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ali keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Abid drives it to mid off.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on leg, Ali looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Masood blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Shan defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Masood punches it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length delivery on middle, Masood defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid plays it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on off, Ali drives it to mid off.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery on off, Abid makes room and slaps it through covers for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Masood plays it towards covers for a run.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abid defends it out.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Masood drives it towards mid on off the back foot.
Full again on middle, Shan drives it to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Masood looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Shan blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid drives it to mid on.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Abid drives it to covers.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid drives it towards mid on.

Flighted delivery on off, Abid plays it towards point and takes the single. The fielder picks the ball and fires a direct hit at the keeper's end. It is referred upstairs. Replays show that the batsman was well in.
Loopy delivery on middle, Masood drives it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Abid drives it back towards the bowler.
Full again on off, Abid drives it towards mid off.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Ali defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, Abid flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Abid looks to cut but gets a top edge on this one. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Abid drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Pakistan are into the lead. Flighted delivery on middle, Abid plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary. The hosts lead by 2 runs.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid blocks it off the back foot.

Fifty for Abid Ali! What a selection this has been. He has toiled hard in the domestic circuit and now that he has got a call up to the national side. He scored a century in the first Test and now has followed it up with a brisk fifty. This has been a very good knock from Abid. He raises his bat and removes his helmet as his teammates applaud his efforts. Full ball on off, Abid drives it through point and gets a couple to bring up his maiden Test fifty. Time to refocus and convert this into a hundred.
Good length ball on off, Abid blocks it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Masood looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Masood blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Masood looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery on off, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Starts with a floated delivery on off, Shan flicks it but finds short mid-wicket.
On the pads, Masood flicks it through mid-wicket. They run the couple and there is a late call for the third from Abid. Shgan responds well and they get it with ease.
Floated on off, Shan defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Abid calmly defends it.
Flighted on off, Abid milks it down to long on for one.
Slightly shorter around off, Masood taps it towards point and looks for a run but he's rightfully sent back.
On a good length on middle, Abid defends it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Abid drives it to mid off.
Bowls a bouncer, Abid does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it through wide mid on for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Abid plays it to point.
Good length delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Masood defends it out.
SIX! Shan brings up the 100-run opening stand in style! He uses his feet to perfection. Floated on middle, Masood comes down the track and tonks it over the long on fence for a biggie.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on off, Masood nudges it through covers and gets a single. Moves to 999 Test runs.
Around the pads, Abid tucks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Glorious shot! Floated around off, Abid gets on his front foot and creams it through covers for a boundary!
Full delivery on middle, Masood drives it to mid on.
On a good length and just outside off, Masood looks to flick but misses it. The keeper appeals for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head. Ultra Edge shows that there is nothing on it.
Bowls it wide outside off, Masood looks to go after it but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Masood looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery on middle, Masood defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Shan defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid drives it through covers for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Masood blocks it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs. 1000 Test runs for Shan Masood. It has been a great achievement for him.
Loopy delivery on off, Shan drives it to mid off.
Flighted delivery on off, Masood defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Masood drives it through mid on for a single.

Fifty for Shan Masood! His 7th in Test cricket. A much needed one for him as he was under tremendous pressure but this will give him more confidence. He knows that the job is not done though and he will look to convert this into a big hundred. Length ball around off, Masood dabs it to third man and gets a single. He raises his bat as he gets applauded.
Bowls a bumper, Masood ducks under it.
Outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Masood looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off, Shan offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Masood drives it towards mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid drives it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Abid keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Abid blocks it well.
Full delivery on off, Abid drives it towards mid off for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Shan defends it out.

NOT OUT! Height looked an issue and it is the issue. Sri Lanka lose one of their two reviews. Can't blame Sri Lanka for going for the review. It looked very close to the naked eye. A similar delivery which got rid of Abid in the first innings. Pacy inswinging ball pitching around off and coming back in. Abid looks to defend but misses and the ball hits him on the pads over the knee roll. The Sri Lankan players put in a huge, confident appeal but the umpire turns it down. Karunaratne signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge confirms no spike. Time for the decisive Ball Tracker and it shows that the ball was going over the stumps.
Good length ball on off, Abid blocks it.
Fiery delivery. 148.9 kph ball outside off, Abid looks to defend but misses.
Good shot! Back of a length around off, Abid gets on the top of the bounce and punches it through covers for three.
Short ball, Masood pulls it away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Bouncer! Ali sways away from it.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Masood plays it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on off, Shan punches it to point.
SIX! Amazing shot. Loopy delivery on off, Masood comes down the track and lofts it over long off for a biggie.
Full delivery on middle, Shan drives it to mid on.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Masood blocks it well.
FOUR! Wonderful shot. Full and outside off, Abid drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
FOUR! Solid stroke! Full delivery on off, Abid drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Ali looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat. It goes towards mid on.
Bowls a bouncer, Ali easily ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, Abid drives it towards mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery just outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
On a good length on off, Ali keeps it out.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Shan taps it towards point and takes a single.
Length delivery outside off, Ali punches it through point for a single.
Short of a length delivery, Masood pulls it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Short delivery again, Shan pulls it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on middle, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery on off, Abid drives it through covers for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Ali defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Abid keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Abid drives it through mid off for a run.
On a good length on off, Abid taps it through point for a run.
FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Masood looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary. 150-run stand between Shan Masood and Abid Ali.
Short delivery outside off, Masood cuts it through point for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through square leg for a run.
On a length on off, Masood taps it through point. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on off, Abid taps it towards point.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Floated delivery on off, Shan defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Masood defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Shan drives it towards covers.
Tossed up delivery on off, Masood drives it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
SIX! Amazing shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Abid plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a maximum.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Masood looks to defend but misses it.
On a length on middle, Shan flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Length delivery on middle, Ali tucks it towards square leg for a run.
On a length on middle, Shan nudges it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery on off, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery outside off, Abid punches it through point for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Good shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Abid plays a slog sweep over square leg for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on middle, Shan keeps it out. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Fernando starts with a good length ball around off, Abid defends it back to the bowler coming forward.
In the channel and outside off, shaping away. Abid covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and just outside off, driven to mid off.

FOUR! Drilled through point. A fuller ball outside off, Ali throws the kitchen sink at the ball and sends it whistling past the cover fielder. Just 1 hit away form his second Test ton. Pakistan's lead touches 100 now.
Around off on a length, Abid strokes it to mid off.
Outside off, Ali makes a leave.
Embuldeniya starts with a ball around off, he keeps it out.
Flatter one on middle, tucked towards short leg.
Around off, tapped towards backward square leg for a single. Abid on strike now.
Around off, Ali pushes it to long off and takes a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated around off, Masood comes down the track and chips it over the bowler's head. The long on fielder comes across and cleans up the ball. A couple for Masood.
Wide outside off, Abid watchfully lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and outside off, Abid this time drives it through gully for a single to move to 99. Showing a lot of patience.
Closer to off pole on a length, Shan lets it be.
Goes little too wide outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
This time outside off on a fullish length. Shan is not lured into the shot as he makes another leave.
Outside off again, another leave from Shan.
Fuller and around off, Abid pushes it towards mid off.
On off and on a fullish length, Ali defends it nicely.
Flatter and just outside off, Ali once again blocks. Not in a hurry at all.

There it is! Second Test ton for Abid Ali in as many games. What a blistering start to his Test career. He could not convert the start he got in the first innings but he is growing into his game so well. He takes the helmet off and raises both his hands towards the crowd to soak all the applauds he is getting. The dressing room is on their feet. He gets there by sweeping this fuller ball towards fine leg and scampers back for the second. He has arrived and how well. What a knock this one. Now, he will look to convert this one into a massive one.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted around off and middle, Ali strokes it back to the bowler.
Fuller and just outside off, driven to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length and outside off, Masood makes another leave.
Landed on middle, Shan strokes it to the left of the bowler and thinks of a single but decides against it.
Nice shot but equally well fielded. Short and wide outside off, Shan cuts it past the backward point. However, the fielder in the deep dives to his right and saves a couple for his side.
Around off on a length, tapped towards point for a single.
Full on the pads, Shan clips it towards deep mid-wicket and scampers for a couple of runs.
Quicker and shorter on the pads, Masood goes back and works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Around off, defended.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, Ali dead-bats it in front of his eyes.
FOUR! Poor ball and dealt with severity. Short ball on middle, Abid rocks back and hammers it to the wide long on fence.
Fullish and outside off, Masood lets it be.

Edgy four! Fernando draws the outside edge but it races to the third man fence. Good length ball just outside off, Shan comes forward to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the second slip for a boundary. Shan enters into the 90s. 200-run stand is up between the two. What a performance so far from these two.
Outside off, left alone.

Almost! A good length ball coming in with the angle. Masood looks to defend again but the ball takes the inside edge and goes almost to the stumps. Shan is not sure where it went as he looks behind. Luckily for him, it went just past the off pole.
Around off, Masood comes forward and defends.
Full and outside off, driven to mid off.
On the pads, Abid tucks it towards fine leg. Shan thinks for a single but Abid shows no response.
Flatter and on the pads, Ali works it towards the leg side and takes a single.
Flighted and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full and down the leg side, Masood goes for the sweep but misses.
Full and on the pads, Shan flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on the pads, pushed to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Masood works it towards mid-wicket and picks up a couple.
Full delivery outside the off stump line, Masood makes a leave to the keeper.
Fullish in length on middle, Shan looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge towards mid-wicket. Another couple taken.
Nicely played! Good length ball outside off, Shan punches it to sweeper cover and picks up another couple. Moves to 98 with that.
Good length ball on middle, Shan flicks it to mid-wicket and moves to 99 with that single.
Outside off, left alone by Abid.

Test ton for Masood now. His second too. Not in as many games but this one will give him a lot of confidence. He had starts during the Australia tour but he could not convert there but he has done it here. He has been around for a while in red-ball cricket. He has taken quite some time to get to the three figure mark in Tests. Shortish length ball around off, Masood taps it towards backward point and takes a quick single. He takes off the helmet and soaks all the applauds. Brilliant, brilliant innings this one.
Fuller and on middle, Ali drives it though mid on for a single.
Full toss on off, Masood drives it to long on for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off, it is defended.
Fuller and on the pads, worked towards deep square leg for a single.
Shortish length ball on middle, Abid taps it off the back foot towards mid on.
Short and outside off, Abid punches it through point for a single.
Fuller length ball on the pads, Masood clips it towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
Landed around off, Abid pushes it to long on.
Good length on off, it is defended.
Full and on off, driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Outside off, pushed to deep cover for a single.
Flighted on middle, flicked to square leg.
Tossed on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on middle, Ali looks to flick it but it goes off the leading edge towards the off side. The batters take a single.
Short ball outside off, Masood punches it to point.
Driven through mid off by the batsman.
Full delivery on middle, Abid pushes it to mid on for nothing.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside the off stump line, Abid looks to cut it off the back foot but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery on off, Ali pushes it to mid off. No run.
Full toss on middle, Ali does not make use of it and pushes it to mid on.
Abid solidly defends the good length ball on middle to mid on.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Abid works it to the leg side.
Flighted ball on middle, Shan defends it out.
On off, pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on middle, Masood works it to long on for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Ali plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on off, Abid defends it to point.
Ali pushes a flighted ball back to the bowler.
Fullish ball outside off, Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Masood pushes it to cover for nothing.
Outside off, left alone by the batsman.
SHOT! Full delivery in the channel, Shan leans forward and drives it through covers. The fielder from deep point comes across and cleans it up. 2 runs taken.
On a length outside off, Masood cuts it to deep point and picks up a single.
Good length ball on middle, Ali tucks it to deep mid-wicket. The fielder from fine leg has to make a lot of ground to cover and that allows the batters to take three.
Flighted ball outside off, Perera drives it to deep extra cover and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Ali drives it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up on middle and leg, Abid works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked solidly by Abid Ali.
Floated ball on middle, Ali whips it to the leg side.
Loopy ball on middle, Ali flicks it to mid on for another dot.
Starts with a floated ball on middle and leg, Masood works it to mid on.
MISFIELD! Tossed up ball on middle, Masood plays it towards mid on where the fielder misfields allowing the batters to take a single.
WIDE! Very rarely you see this in Tests! Lasith bowls a very wide delivery down the leg side, Abid lets it go. It is wided.
Floated delivery on the pads, Abid looks to flick it but misses to get hit on the pads.
Loopy delivery on middle and leg, Ali works it to long on and picks up a couple. The fielder comes across and cleans it up. Easy runs coming for Pakistan.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. They pick up a single.
Floated ball on middle, Masood tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on off, Abid looks to drive but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards square leg.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle and leg, defended back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up outside off, Abid pushes it to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Ali whips it to square leg for nothing.
Full delivery on middle, Ali pushes it back to the bowler. Perera fails to collecxt it cleanly. Ali wants the single but is sent back. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but Aki was well in.
Floated ball on middle and leg, Masood looks to sweep it but gets hit on the pads. No harm done.
SIX! Beautiful batting! Floated ball on middle, Masood comes down the track and hammers it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
MISFIELD! Full delivery down the leg side, Masood plays the paddle sweep to short fine leg. Dilruwan Perera lets the ball through his legs and allows the batters to take a single.
FOUR! Poor bowling! Loopy ball down the leg side yet again, Abid bends and sweeps it past the short fine leg fielder for a boundary.
Floated ball on middle, Ali sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
The batsman has driven it through mid on. One run added to the total.
Floated ball on middle and leg, Masood works it to mid-wicket. Abid wants the single but Shan says no.
Tossed up ball on off, Masood drives it to long off for a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Ali defends it to point and takes a single.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Masood tucks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle, Masood works it to the leg side and picks up a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Loopy ball outside off, Abid drives it to cover where the fielder tumbles to make a stop.
Floated ball on middle, Ali works it to the leg side.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Poor poor bowling this down the leg side, Abid sweeps it towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
Floated ball on off, Masood defends it to cover for a dot.
Masood pushes this tossed up ball on middle back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Shan defends it out.
Outside off, pushed it to cover for nothing.
Floated ball on middle, Shan defends it out.
Shorter delivery outside off, Masood punches it to deep cover and picks up a single.
Flighted ball on the pads, Masood sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Another misfield! Flighted ball on middle, Abid sweeps it to mid-wicket where the fielder commits another misfield, allowing the batters to take a couple.
Tossed up ball on the leg stump line, Abid looks to defend it but gets hit on the pads after hitting the inside edge. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Easy picking! Darted on the pads, Ali flicks it nicely towards the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Full toss on middle, Abid works it to short fine leg. No run.
Floated on off, Shan defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Shan defends it towards mid on.
Short outside off, Masood cuts it through point and gets a couple.
Once again off, Masood blocks it.
Floated on off, Masood defends it onto the ground.
Around the pads, SM glances it through the on side and takes a brace to take the partnership to 262.
Full delivery outside off, Ali drives it nicely but finds the cover fielder. No run.
Back of a length ball on off, Ali rocks on his back foot and defends it to cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Slower delivery outside off, left alone by Abid.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled! Kumara bowls it on a length outside off, Abid looks to defend it but misses it completely.
Flatter delivery outside off, Masood punches it to cover and picks up a single.
Floated ball on off, Ali defends it off the back foot to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Ali defends it to point and takes a single.
Quicker delivery outside off, Masood pushes it to long off for a single.
WIDE! Bowls another floated delivery way down the leg side, Abid looks to sweep it but misses it. The umpire signals it a wide for bowling a negative line.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on off, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off, Masood punches it to deep cover and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across to clean it up.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Masood guides it to deep point for a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Abid lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, Abid makes another good leave to the keeper.
FOUR! Beautiful! Pakistan are making merry out there as nothing is happening off the pitch. Short of a length ball outside off, Masood cuts it off the back foot to deep point for a boundary.
On middle and leg, Masood whips it to the leg side.
Floated ball on the pads, Masood works it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Ali defends it out.
Tossed up ball on middle, Abid pushes it down to long on and takes a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Abid works it to deep square leg for a single.
Short delivery on middle, Masood pulls it to backward square leg for a couple.

OUT! Caught! Finally. Finally there is a wicket. It has taken a long, long time to get a wicket. The mammoth opening stand has been broken and Shan walks away but after a great knock. Kumara has done the trick and right on the stroke of Tea. It is the short ball which has done the damage. Kumara bowls the effort delivery and it is directed well as well. Right around the body. Masood is taken by surprise. Maybe he expected Lahiru to be tired and did not expect a short one. He is late in his pull and he ends up hitting it in  the air straight to the man at deep mid-wicket. Oshada Fernando there comes running in and takes a good catch. The 278-run partnership is broken. Pakistan lose their first wicket with the lead of 198.
Full delivery outside off, Azhar makes a good leave to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Azhar pushes it to point and wants the single but Abid says no. There was an easy run there.
FOUR! What a way to get off the mark! Full delivery on middle, Azhar drives it straight past the bowler for a boundary. The lead for Pakistan crosses 200. It is TEA ON DAY 3.
Starts with a flighted ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on middle, Abid works it to deep mid-wicket and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Loopy ball on off, Abid pushes it to cover and takes a single.
FOUR! Deft touch! Very full delivery down the leg side, Azhar bends on his knees and paddle sweeps it through fine leg for a boundary.
Flatter delivery on middle, Azhar works it to the leg side and picks up a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Starts with a bouncer around middle and leg, Azhar ducks under it. The umpire signals one for the over.
Short ball outside off, Azhar sways away from it. Kumara showing good energy out there.
Back of a length ball outside off, Azhar pushes it to cover for a single.
Uppish but safe! Good length ball outside off, Abid guides it uppishly to backward point and takes a single.
Shorter in length on off, Azhar hops and blocks it out onto the pitch.
Fullish delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Floated ball outside off, Abid opens the face of the bat and plays it to short third man for a single.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled! Loopy delivery outside off, with a little spin on it, Azhar looks to defend it but misses it completely.
On middle, Azhar Ali flicks it to mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Floated ball on middle, Abid pushes it to mid on.
Flatter delivery outside off, Abid defends it off the back foot to cover.
Loopy delivery on off, Abid pushes it to cover for nothing.
Good length ball down the leg side, Azhar lets the ball go to the keeper.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Azhar ducks under it.
On a length outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Azhar hops to flick it but misses it to get hit on the arm guard. The ball rolls towards the off side.

Short of a length delivery down the leg side, Azhar lets it go to the keeper. The keeper puts in a huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. Kumara suggests that it might have clipped his body on the way.
Wide down the leg side, the batsman leaves it alone.
Floated ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on off, Abid cuts it off the back foot to point.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Abid plays the paddle sweep down to fine leg and picks up a couple. Kumara comes across and cleans it up.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.

BEATEN! That is nicely bowled! Tosses this one up around off which spins away from the batsman, Abid Ali attempts to defend it but goes past the outside edge of the bat and into the gloves of the keeper.
Outside off, pushed to point.
BOUNCER! Another one around middle and leg, Azhar has no problems in ducking under it.
Short ball around off, Azhar sways away from it.

DROPPED! An easy catch dropped by Oshada Fernando at short leg. It should have been taken at this level. Good length ball on middle, Azhar flicks it towards short leg but Oshada was not expecting it and makes a mess of it. Lahiru Kumara is down on his knees showing his disappointment.
Good length delivery on middle, Azhar defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Azhar Ali stands tall and defends it out.
The batsman has punched that ball through the off side.
Embuldeniya bowls it short and wide, Abid cuts it well but straight to point.
On middle, it is pushed back to the bowler.

Quicker and outside off, Ali this time goes on the back foot and runs it down to third man. It is racing towards the fence but Perera from short third man races and makes a sliding stop. The batters take three.
Fuller ball around off, Ali pushes it towards mid off and takes a single. 300 up for Pakistan.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball around off, it is defended.
Starts with a full delivery on off, Azhar pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from the skipper! Flighted ball outside off, Azhar leans forward and creams the drive through the covers for a boundary.
Flatter delivery on middle, Azhar works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On middle and leg, Abid whips it to square leg.
Tossed up ball on middle, Abid pushes it to long on and moves to 148 with that single.
Floated ball on middle, Azhar works it to square leg.
Flighted ball on off, Abid pushes it to cover for nothing.
Floated ball down the leg side, Abid plays the sweep to short fine leg for a single.

NOT OUT! It has gone straight off the bat! What a waste of a review from the visitors. Some desperation shown by the Lankans. Flighted ball on middle, Azhar defends it back to the bowler. The Lankans think that the ball had hit the pad first and they, after thinking for ages go for the review. The replays roll in and it clearly confirms that it had gone straight off the bat to the bowler. Sri Lanka have lost both of their reviews now.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. One run added to the total.
Floated ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Full ball on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Flatter on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket for a run.
Fuller and on middle, Abid flicks it nicely but finds the short mid-wicket.
On middle, flicked to the mid-wicket fielder again.

There's the 150. He once again takes his helmet off and raises both his arms to accept the applause. What an innings this has been from the 2-Test old Abid. He gets there by driving this fuller ball firmly to mid off. Can he convert this one into a double now? He would love to do so.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Around middle, pushed to mid off.
Down the leg side, Abid looks to tuck it around the corner but misses.

Huge appeal for LBW but not out says the umpire. Sri Lanka do not have a review left. They'd hope that this is not going to hit the stumps or they will rue the lost review. A fuller ball around off, Ali goes for the sweep but makes no connection. They appeal but not out says the umpire. The replays roll in and luckily for the Lankans, it pitched outside off and also, did not go to the stumps.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, it is defended.
Fullish and on off, Ali keeps it out.
Shortish around off, Ali taps it to long off for a single.
Shortish and outside off, tapped through covers for a run.
Good length ball on middle and off. It has little to no movement. Azhar flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a three as the fielder cleans it up before the ropes.
Poor ball. It is down the leg side, Abid looks to flick but misses. Little bit of bat and it would have gone to the fence.
Back of a length on off, Abid punches it back to the bowler.
On the pads, Abid looks to flick but misses. The ball lobs of his pad and goes to the on side. They steal a leg bye.
Flighted ball outside off, Abid drives it through covers for a couple before the fielder can reach it to clean it up.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up ball on off, Abid plays it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Azhar defends it to point for a dot ball.

Floated ball outside off, Azhar lets the ball go to the keeper.

Pure timing! Full delivery on middle, Abid works it to deep square leg. The fielder from fine leg comes across, puts in a good sliding stop and saves a boundary for his side. The batters still manage to take three.
Fullish delivery on off, Azhar pushes it to cover.
Fullish delivery on off, Azhar drives it to point.
Beautifully played! Fernando bowls a full delivery on middle and leg, Azhar whips it nicely to deep mid-wicket but it will not reach the fence as the fielder comes across  and collects.

Good length ball on middle, Azhar tucks it to deep mid-wicket and takes off for a couple. The fielder runs to his from deep square leg, collects it and has a shy at the bowler's end. Abid slips after reaching the crease but gets up quickly. 50-run stand is up between the two.
Floated ball outside off, Abid drives it to deep cover for a single.
Outside off, Azhar lets the ball go to the keeper.
Loopy ball outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter ball outside off, Azhar punches it to the off side.
On off, pushed to cover.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azhar defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery way outside off, Abid lets the ball go to the keeper.
Abid makes another leave to this good length ball outside the off stump line.
Fullish ball outside off, Abid shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Abid Ali pushes it to long on for nothing.
Fuller one way outside off again, Abid does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go behind.
Outside off, Abid lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flatter delivery outside off, Azhar drives it to cover where the fielder is not able to collect it cleanly. The batters manage to take a single. The lead is now 250.
Shorter delivery outside off, Azhar rocks on his back foot and pushes it to deep cover for a single.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. One run added to the total.
On middle, defended back to Embuldeniya.
Shorter delivery outside off, Abid cuts it off the back foot to the off side for a single.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! That is some poor fielding! Fullish delivery outside off, Abid drives it through covers and Dhananjaya de Silva is chasing after it from deep point. He slides and stops the ball. It is rolling inside the fence but de Silva comically pushes the ball back in from outside the fence. The umpires check whether it is a four or not and the replays confirm that it is.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Abid looks to drive it but misses it completely.

FOUR! Poor bowling this! Cannot bowl on the pads to this guy! Full delivery on the pads, Abid flicks it nicely to the deep square leg region for a boundary. There is a fielder stationed at deep mid-wicket but he had no chance.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
FOUR! Hammered! Short of a length ball outside off, Abid stands tall and punches it to the deep cover fence for the third boundary of the over.
Floated ball on off, Azhar pushes it to cover.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azhar defends it out.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Floated ball on middle, Azhar attempts the sweep shot but it goes off the top edge towards deep square leg but luckily for him , it lands safely. A single taken before the fielder reaches it from deep mid-wicket.
On off, pushes it to cover for nothing.
Flighted ball on middle, Abid blocks it out.

Good length ball down the leg side, Azhar looks to flick it but misses it.

FOUR! That is thrashed! Brilliant batting. Kumara bowls a half volley on off, Azhar dismisses this through mid off for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar works it to the leg side.
Back of a length ball on middle, Azhar works it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Abid tucks it to backward square leg for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.

Short delivery outside off, Azhar punches it to the off side for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle and leg, Azhar leans forward and blocks it out.
OHH! Floated on off, Azhar looks to drive it but it hits the outside edge of the bat and it goes towards deep cover for a couple.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan lose their review but no one can raise a finger on Abid Ali because he has played a gem of a knock. Everyone in the stadium is up on its feet as he walks off. Similar way he got out in the previous innings. Fast and pacy delivery pitching around off. It jags back in, Abid looks to defend but gets beaten by the pace of it and the ball hits him on the pads. Sri Lankan players go up in a huge appeal and the umpire slowly raises his finger. Abid knows he is a goner but after talking to his partner, he signals the 'T' in the eleventh hour. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows there is no involvement of the bat. Ball Tracker then comes in and it shows all red as  the ball was going onto crash the middle stump. To the dismay of everyone, Abid will have to walk back but what a fine player he is. He will be disappointed not to get to his double century. But it has been a great knock and he has put his side in a great position in this game. He walks back looking as fresh as he came out to bat in  the first day of this Test. Though he is 32, he looks like a fine player and one feels he will be a big player for this side for a few years to come.

Beauty to welcome Babar. It is a yorker on off, Azam jams it out. The ball hits the inner half of his bat and goes towards the stumps but it hits his shoe and stays on the crease. People in the stadium had their hearts in the mouth.
Length ball outside off, Azam leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Babar drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller on off, Babar defends it from the crease.
Huge cheer from the crowd as their hero, Babar Azam is off the mark.

On middle and leg, Azhar tucks it to the leg side.
Loopy ball on the pads, Azhar works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Stand and deliver! Babar Azam showing his class! Back of a length delivery outside off, Azam just stands tall and punches it to deep cover for a boundary. First one for him in this innings.
Kumara retaliates by bowling a short of a length delivery outside off, Azam though is ready for it and sways away from it.
On a length on middle, Azam tucks it to square leg for a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Azhar ducks under it.
Good length delivery on the pads, Azhar works it fine and takes a couple. The fielder from fine leg comes across and cleans it up.
On middle, Ali tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Ali defends it to the leg side and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Babar defends it back to the bowler off the back foot.
On off, Babar pushes this past the diving cover fielder for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Ali works it to the leg side and takes a single.
Full toss on the pads, Azam whips it nicely through mid-wicket and takes three. The fielder runs after it and cleans it up.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Floated ball on middle, Babar pushes it to mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed to long on for a single.
Tossed up ball on off, Azhar pushes it to point for a single.

Overthrows! Loopy ball on middle, Babar whips it to deep mid-wicket and calls Ali for a couple. The fielder there throws it to the bowler who does not collect and neither the two fielders backing up. Three taken in the end.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ali whips it to backward square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Almost! Flighted ball around off, Azhar looks to cut it but it is too close and it beats the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

FIFTY! Azhar Ali scores one after 14 Test match innings. A welcome return to form for the skipper. Flatter delivery outside off, Ali pushes it to deep cover and picks up a single. Can he too, like the openers, score a ton here?
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total.
Short ball outside off, Ali punches it to the off side and two runs have been taken.
Flat delivery outside off, Azhar lets the ball go to the keeper.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Floated ball on middle, Azam works it to the leg side for a single.
On middle, pushed down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Azam blocks it out to the off side.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azam whips it to square leg and picks up a single.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Azhar whips it in front of square for another run.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, Azam looks to flick it but it goes off the leading edge back to the bowler. He collects it on the bounce.
Flatter delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azhar sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Brilliant bowling this from Lasith! Floated ball outside off spinning away, Azam looks to defend but misses it.
Loopy on middle, Azam defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Babar comes down the pitch and pushes it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Azam pushes it to long on for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Babar punches it to deep cover for a single.
On off, Ali defends it onto the pitch.
Loopy delivery on middle and leg, Ali whips it to mid-wicket.
Tosses this one up on middle, Azhar whips it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Looped up ball outside off, Azhar looks to drive it but fails to get any bat on it.
Loopy ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off, Babar pushes it to cover.
Tossed up ball on middle, Azam pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter one outside off, Babar punches it to cover for nothing.
Loopy ball on middle, Babar plays it to the leg side for a single.
On off, pushed to deep cover for a single.
Full toss on middle, Babar defends it out.

Tosses this one up on middle and leg, Azhar whips it to square leg for a single.
Full on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted on middle, Azam defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out solidly by Azam.
Loopy ball on middle, Azhar defends it back to Lasith.
Azhar defends this flighted ball on middle and leg to the leg side.
Outside off, defended off the front foot by Azhar Ali.
